headline: Nasdaq Leans Into Fintech Model With AWS, Eqlipse And IPO Fast Entry
summary: Nasdaq (NasdaqGS:NDAQ) is expanding its fintech capabilities through a cloud partnership with Amazon Web Services and plans to introduce 23/5 trading hours. Japan Exchange Group's Osaka Exchange is adopting Nasdaq's Eqlipse technology for its derivatives platform. Nasdaq has proposed a "fast entry" rule to bring large IPOs into its key indexes more quickly after listing. Nasdaq sits at the center of global equity trading, and these moves signal a broad refresh of how its platforms operate...
